    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>August 17 1863</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revnd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philad.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p>You will please send me the following books.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">50-60 Copies <persName>Peixottos</persName> Catechism of the
                    <sic>Bibel</sic></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">' do Instruction Elementary Intrd.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">' do Thoughts on <persName>Poibel</persName> Text</p>
            <p>I have written to day directed to <persName>Miss Peixotto</persName><lb/> but, as
                    <sic>i</sic> have not had the full address <sic>i</sic><lb/> fear the letter
                will not be received in time<lb/> and as <sic>i</sic> was told that you are the
                Agent<lb/> for those books, and as <sic>i</sic> want them to be<lb/> send
                    <sic>emidiatly</sic> as <sic>i</sic> have to send them <sic>of</sic> by<lb/>
                Steamer on <date>Wednesday</date>, you would oblige me<lb/>
                <sic>verry</sic> much if you would send those books<lb/> by Express
                    <sic>emidiatly</sic>, and have collection made<lb/> on delivery I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Sigmund Jacobs</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <placeName>No 194. Pearl <sic>street</sic></placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
